name: Unidentified_Tusken_Raider_warrior_(Boba_Fett)

attributes.name: Died
values: Between c. 5 ABY and c. 9 ABY

content:
A female Tusken Raider warrior was a member of a tribe of Tusken Raiders on the planet Tatooine around 4 ABY. When the prisoner Boba Fett attempted to escape the tribe's camp, the warrior defeated him in a duel, allowing the rest of her tribe to recapture their captive. After Fett killed a sand beast, he was accepted to the tribe. The warrior instructed Fett how to fight with a Gaderffii stick.
After the newly-initiated Boba Fett left to see the Pyke Syndicate in Mos Eisley, the Pykes massacred the tribe, including the warrior. They painted the symbol of a speeder bike gang known as the Kintan Striders to put the blame on them. Per Tusken tradition, Fett gathered all the bodies and weapons and burned them at a funeral pyre. Fett later attacked the Kintan Striders, killing several of their members, in revenge.
The Tusken warrior made her first appearance in a flashback sequence of the The Book of Boba Fett's premiere episode "Chapter 1: Stranger in a Strange Land," which began streaming to Disney+ on December 29, 2021. She was portrayed by Joanna Bennett.
